<h2 id="220">9. Creating a dummy item for cash sales</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You may find that items are to be sold that do not have a data record in plentymarkets. Create a dummy item to be able to sell these items anyway. The POS user then adds the dummy item to the POS shopping cart and edits the name and price of the item. To do so, you need a dummy item for each of the VAT rates that apply to the products in your portfolio. When you create this item, go to the <strong>Settings</strong> tab of the variation and for the option <strong>Limitation</strong> select the setting <strong>Do not administer stock for this variation</strong>. Save the item for this setting to take effect. For further information about creating items, refer to the <a href="/item/managing-items"><strong>Managing items</strong>  </a> page of the manual.</p>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock important">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-important" title="Important"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Activating rights for POS functions</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>To allow POS users to work with dummy items, go to <strong>Settings » Basic settings » User » Accounts » Open account » Tab: Right » Tab: Mobile</strong>. In the <strong>POS functions</strong> area, activate the rights <strong>Edit price</strong> and <strong>Rename order item</strong>.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
